  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Supply Chain Planner",
  "description": "<p><strong>about the company</strong><br /><br />Our client, a global leader in the MedTech sector, is seeking an Supply Chain Planner to lead their service-parts optimization strategy. In this role, you will balance mission-critical spare parts availability with lean inventory principles to drive capital efficiency and reduce carrying costs.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br /><u>Inventory Strategy & Planning</u></p><p>Design and maintain robust stocking plans for spare parts to ensure 100% part availability for mission-critical medical equipment.</p><p>Continuously refine reorder logic and economic order quantities (EOQ) based on evolving usage patterns and data-led projections.</p><p>Lead the \"Change Management\" process for inventory, ensuring technical upgrades (via ECR/TB) do not result in obsolete stock or service gaps.</p><p><u>Demand forecasting</u><br /><br />Leverage historical data and maintenance schedules to predict future spare part needs, reducing \"stock-out\" risks and emergency freight costs.</p><p>Partner with Service Engineering leads to synchronize inventory levels with planned preventative maintenance and upcoming project rollouts.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>NITEC or Diploma, or equivalent qualification in Supply Chain Management or a related field </li><li>Minimum of 2 years’ relevant working experience </li></ul><p>If you are interested in the position, kindly apply to this job or send your CVs to noelle.ng@randstad.com.sg</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted</p><p>EA: 94C3609 / R1982617</p>",
